author: Inside Edition
description: TSA agents have been working without a paycheck for five weeks ever since the government shut down. They are getting supplies of food from local food banks and other organizations. Inside Edition's Les Trent spoke to TSA agent Lashanda Palmer, who works at Philadelphia International Airport. Transportation Secretary Sean Duffy has ordered a 4% cutback in flights starting Friday. It will grow to 10% if the shutdown continues into next week. Travel expert Pauline Frommer spoke with Trent.
title: TSA Agents Get Support From Food Banks Amid Government Shutdown

author: Inside Edition
description: Kitkat, a neighborhood legend, has been killed by a Waymo. Fans of the adored feline are taking to social media to demand justice for Kitkat. The cat was a fixture at Randa's Market in San Francisco. There is a growing memorial in front of the store. Driverless robocars like Waymo are controversial, and already the target of a lot of anger on the streets in San Francisco and other cities. Waymo said Kitkat darted underneath the driverless taxi and expressed their sympathies to the cat’s owner.
title: Driverless Waymo Car Kills Adored Neighborhood Cat, Kitkat

author: Inside Edition
description: The cast of "Stranger Things" hit the red carpet to celebrate the final season of the popular Netflix series. Stars Millie Bobby Brown and David Harbour seemed relaxed in each other's company. Fans pointed out earlier this week that published reports claimed 21-year-old Brown filed a "harassment and bullying claim" with "pages and pages of accusations" against 50-year-old Harbour, who plays her dad on the show.
title: Millie Bobby Brown And David Harbour Pose Together On Red Carpet

author: Inside Edition
description: Sydney Sweeney stopped by The Late Show with Stephen Colbert to promote her boxing movie "Christie." She revealed she's been trying out new things this year, including skydiving. Jennifer Lawrence made her long-awaiting return to the Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon after eight years. Fans of Jimmy Kimmel watched a re-run of the show after ABC pulled the plug on Thursday night's new episode. Online chatter says a "personal matter" with the host forced the cancellation.
title: Sydney Sweeney on Late Show, Jennifer Lawrence on Tonight Show

author: Inside Edition
description: A woman was awakened by noises in her New Jersey apartment to see strangers walking away. After confronting them, the men explained that they were not intruders and that they were doing an inspection. It turned out the men work at her apartment building. Inside Edition spoke to 21-year-old Rebecca Thermidor. The building's managers say they sent Thermidor an email explaining they needed access to her apartment the morning they entered.
title: Naked Woman Wakes To Find 3 Male Inspectors In Her Apartment

author: Inside Edition
description: A drug company executive suddenly collapsed in the Oval Office. Others, including Dr. Oz rushed to help. Health Secretary, Robert F. Kennedy Jr. appeared to flee. The White House is defending Kennedy Friday saying "the secretary rushed to get medical assistance," and called one journalist a "ghoul" for suggesting Kennedy ran off. Meanwhile, Kennedy's cousin, Michael Skakel, who served 11 years in prison for the murder of his 15-year-old neighbor Martha Moxley is speaking out for the first time.
title: Did RFK Jr Flee After Executive Collapsed in Oval Office?

author: Inside Edition
description: People are going bonkers for teddy bear glass cups at Starbucks. The 20-ounce holiday bottled called "Bearista Cold Cups," debuted Thursday and immediately sold out. It is a clear, bear-shaped bottle with a green beanie and a Starbucks logo on its belly. It sells for $29.99, but those looking for one may have to be prepared to spend a lot more. On eBay, they're selling for up to $550. For many, Starbucks' bear cup is a bear necessity.
title: Craze Over Starbuck's 'Bearista Cold Cups'

author: Inside Edition
description: Some cops' jobs were made easier when this suspect fell right into their laps. Police in Indian River County, Florida, say the suspect was tracked down, suspected of having a stolen truck. Cops say when they approached him outside the residence and identified themselves, he ran into the house and barricaded himself in. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Suspect Falls Through Ceiling Of House While Cops Search For Him In Florida

author: Inside Edition
description: Spelunkers found a giant spider 'super-city' in a cave on the border of Greece and Albania. The massive webbed structure, in the depths of the Sulfur Cave, is over 100 square meters, consisting of thousands of funnel-shaped webs. The lead researcher studying the arachnid habitat says it's likely the largest spider web in the world. Scientists say it's home to an estimated 11,000 spiders, from two different species, including the barn funnel weaver.
title: Check Out 'Spider City,' The Largest Spider Web Ever Found

author: Inside Edition
description: Teacher Abby Zwerner sued the former assistant principal, Ebony Parker, at her school claiming that she failed to act after four people told her Zwerner's 6-year-old student had brought a gun to school.
title: Jury Awards $10 Million To Teacher Shot By 1st Grader #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: There's international uproar after Mexican President Claudia Sheinbaum was groped in public. Each day, thousands of women suffer the silent indignity of getting groped in public. Former NYPD detective David Sarni showed Inside Edition what to do if a groper comes close.
title: What To Do If A Groper Gets Close To You #shorts
